headlines.description: — Kemba Walker matched his season high with 32 points and the Boston Celtics rolled to a 99-86 victory over the Phoenix Suns on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Walker ties season high with 32 points, Celtics beat Suns

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Orlando Magic

headlines.description: — Zion Williamson scored 23 points in 23 minutes in his first game against Orlando, and the New Orleans Pelicans beat the Magic 135-100 on Thursday night to snap a four-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Williamson scores 23, helps Pelicans rout Magic 135-100

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo scored 27 points and Khris Middleton had 24 as the Milwaukee Bucks defeated the Philadelphia 76ers 124-117 on Thursday night in a matchup of two of the Eastern Conference's top teams.

events.name: Detroit Pistons at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Derrick White had 26 points, Jakob Poeltl added 17 points and 11 rebounds and the San Antonio Spurs beat the Detroit Pistons 106-91 on Thursday night to snap a five-game home losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Spurs beat Pistons 106-91 to snap 5-game home skid

headlines.description: — Nikola Vucevic scored 18 points and matched a season high with 16 rebounds, Coby White and Thaddeus Young scored 18 apiece, and the Chicago Bulls beat the struggling Charlotte Hornets 108-91 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Vucevic dominates as Bulls pound Hornets 108-91

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic scored 30 points, leading the Dallas Mavericks to a 115-110 victory over the Lakers on Thursday night in the return of Los Angeles star Anthony Davis from a 30-game injury absence.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic, Mavs beat Lakers 115-110 as LA star Davis returns
